Strategic Value Partners, LLC Key Developments

Strategic Value Partners Announces New Appointments
Nov 16 16
Strategic Value Partners, LLC announced the appointment of Goran Puljic, formerly a Partner at Oak Hill Advisors, and David Weaver, formerly Chairman of the Board and CEO of Jefferies International ("Jefferies"), to its Advisory Council. Mr.  Puljicjoins SVPGlobal with 30 years of experience in financial services, primarily in CLOs and structured products. He is a retired Partner of Oak Hill Advisors, where, from 2008 to 2016, he was a Portfolio Manager and Co-head of the Corporate Structured Products Group focusing on investments in CLOs. Mr.  Weaver brings nearly 35 years of financial services experience to SVPGlobal, most recently as Chairman and CEO of Jefferies in London, where he led the firm's European expansion over a nine year period. In this role he more than tripled the size of the firm's European business, focusing on areas of governance, risk management, internal management structure and regulatory affairs.


Strategic Value Partners, LLC Presents at The 19th Annual Europe GRI 2016, Sep-14-2016
Jun 16 16
Strategic Value Partners, LLC Presents at The 19th Annual Europe GRI 2016, Sep-14-2016 . Venue: PARIS, France. Speakers: BRYAN KELLY, Head of Real Estate.


Klöckner Pentaplast Reportedly Mulls US Listing
Sep 7 15
Klöckner Pentaplast GmbH is considering a stock market listing in the United States, sources said. Strategic Value Partners, LLC hired Goldman Sachs and Jefferies  to advise on the deal. Officials at Strategic Value Partners, Klöckner Pentaplast and Goldman Sachs and Jefferies declined to comment to Reuters.


